{"title_page": "2020 coronavirus pandemic in Iowa", "text_new": "{{short description|Details of ongoing pandemic in Iowa, United States}}\n{{Current disaster|event=pandemic|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox pandemic\n| name            = 2020 coronavirus pandemic in Iowa\n| map1            = \n| places          = \n| legend1         = \n| map2            = \n| legend2         = \n| map3            = \n| legend3         = \n| disease         = [[COVID-19]]\n| virus_strain    = [[SARS-CoV-2]]\n| location        = [[Iowa]], U.S.\n| first_case      = [[Iowa City, Iowa|Iowa City]]\n| arrival_date    = March 8, 2020<br />({{Age in years, months, weeks and days|month1=03|day1=8|year1=2020|month2=|day2=|year2=}})\n| origin          = \n| confirmed_cases = 424<ref name=\"idph-official\">{{cite web |title=Emerging Health Issues - Novel Coronavirus\n|url=https://idph.iowa.gov/Emerging-Health-Issues/Novel-Coronavirus |publisher=Iowa Department of Public Health |accessdate=18 March 2020}}</ref>\n| suspected_cases = \n| recovery_cases  = 23\n| deaths          = 6\n| total_ili       = \n| website         = [https://idph.iowa.gov/Emerging-Health-Issues/Novel-Coronavirus Iowa Department of Public Health]\n}}\nThe [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]] was confirmed to have reached the U.S. state of [[Iowa]] in March 2020.\n\n==Timeline==\n* March 9 \u2013 Proclamation of Disaster Emergency signed by Governor [[Kim Reynolds]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.weareiowa.com/article/news/health/coronavirus/8-iowans-test-postivie-for-coronavirus-covid-19/524-982d69c7-c93d-4bac-b65c-96006fbc6ddb|title=32 test negative, 8 test postive for COVID-19|website=weareiowa.com|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-28|first1=Hollie|last1=Schlesselman|date=2020-03-09}}</ref>\n*March 15 \u2013 Governor Reynolds recommends closing schools for four weeks. The state is developing legislation to provide child care during the emergency, including food for low-income students. The total number of confirmed coronaviru